<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENAP70A9301002" svcinfotypenbr = "03" svcinfoqualnbr = "01" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Parking Sensor System Description (If Equipped)
</title>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
The parking sensor system consists of the parking sensor system control module, combination meter, parking sensors, parking sensor buzzer, parking sensor OFF switch, and back up light switch.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
If the parking sensors located on the rear bumper detect an obstacle, the parking sensor system control module causes the parking sensor buzzer to sound.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
The parking sensor system works when the parking sensor OFF switch is in the released (ON) position and the gear is in the reverse position.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
The parking sensor control module communicates with the combination meter via the LIN communication system. (For LIN communication, refer to 
<intxref refid = "AENAP70AA801001">Communication System Description</intxref>
.)
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
DTC for parking sensor control system can be checked by selecting the “Combination Meter / Meter/M&#38;A” on the SUZUKI scan tool.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
